14 SECTION 11. (1) Sections 5, 6 and 8 of this 2026 Act are repealed on January 2, 2031.
15 (2) The repeal of sections 5, 6 and 8 of this 2026 Act does not affect a petition for post-
16 conviction relief described in section 6 of this 2026 Act, filed within the time limitations de-
17 scribed in section 8 of this 2026 Act, for which final judgment has not been entered.
18
19 CAPTIONS
20
21 SECTION 12. The unit captions used in this 2026 Act are provided only for the conven-
22 ience of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this state or express any
23 legislative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
24
25 EMERGENCY CLAUSE
26
27 SECTION 13. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
28 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
29 on its passage.
